description.plain:
Shoreline Mafia is a Los Angeles rap group. Founding members Fenix Flexin and Ohgeesy became friends in high school and created the collective, later adding Master Kato and Rob Vicious. Most of the group’s production is handled by Ron Ron The Producer.

The collective caught the attention of Atlantic Records thanks to its breakout hit “Musty” from the 2017 debut mixtape ShorelineDoThatShit.  They later signed to Atlantic Records in the summer of 2018.

songs.title: Bands

description.plain: “Bands” is one of the singles from Rob Vicious‘ album Traplantic. The song, produced by AceTheFace, is about drugs, getting money, and what the members of Shoreline Mafia plan to do with the money. It is the group’s biggest hit.

songs.title: Musty

description.plain:
“Musty” is the breakout song for the LA-based rap collective known as Shoreline Mafia, off their debut album ShorelineDoThatShit.

On “Musty,” Ohgeesy provides an addicting chorus as he rides the lowkey, bass-heavy, and undeniably West Coast beat produced by notable up and coming producer Ron-Ron. After Ohgeesy’s laid-back yet punctual verse, fellow Shoreline Mafia member Fenix comes in viciously, following his homie’s leaned-out lyrics with more four pouring.
